      "content": {
        "title": "Muscular Dystrophy and Neuropathy — Orthopaedic Management — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Progressive neuromuscular disorders including Duchenne muscular dystrophy and Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease with orthopaedic deformities.",
        "summary": "DMD patients develop contractures and scoliosis; steroid therapy slows decline. CMT causes cavovarus foot requiring bracing or osteotomy."
      },
